interestingcomments.content: Whats the fastest way to browse Q2/SL2 raw DNG files on your computer? /!/ I love shooting on on RAW on my Q2 however the files are usually large (around 90MB) so browsing the files to see which ones are worth keeping takes a while, usually a few seconds just to preview a picture on my Mac. I was wondering if you guys knew a better way to browse quickly through the files other than shooting JPEG+DNG since the jpegs are faster to browse
